    <abstract id="aspace_50449564ea587637ed99361984c62c8c" label="Abstract">Daniel Kraus (1975-) is an American author and filmmaker, best known for his young adult horror and science fiction novels and for his collaborations with filmmakers Guillermo del Toro and George A. Romero. Kraus has directed feature films and documentaries, and has published novels and comic books. The Daniel Kraus Papers document his career as a novelist as well as early childhood fiction, with manuscripts of published novels and notebooks of unpublished juvenilia.</abstract>
